Political bickering has emerged between ODM and Jubilee politicians over President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s Homa Bay tour.Speaking in Homa Bay town on Sunday, Senator Moses Kajwang&rsquo; urged the President to leave behind DP William Ruto during the tour.Kajwang&rsquo; did not disclose the reason why Ruto should not accompany the President.&ldquo;We welcome him but he should exclude Ruto in his entourage,&rdquo; Kajwang&rsquo; said.Uhuru is expected to commission a number of national government projects.Karachuonyo MP James Rege and the county Jubilee co-coordinator Odhiambo Makowiti accused the senator of perpetrating prejudice.Rege said such comments should be avoided.